  "faq": {
    "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "subtitle": "Answers to the most common questions",
    "items": [
      {
        "q": "How can I register?",
        "a": "Fill in our online form on the website or contact us via WhatsApp. Our team will reach you within 24 hours."
      },
      {
        "q": "What documents do I need?",
        "a": "Basic: passport, ID, CV, medical certificate, criminal record. Full list on the documents page."
      },
      {
        "q": "How long does the process take?",
        "a": "On average 4-8 weeks from application to departure, depending on documents and vacancies."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is work experience required?",
        "a": "Experience is preferred for many vacancies, but not always required. We have vacancies for beginners too."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is a passport required?",
        "a": "Yes, an international passport is required. Minimum 12 months validity recommended."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is English or Hebrew required?",
        "a": "Not required. We help with translation and communication."
      },
      {
        "q": "What happens after registration?",
        "a": "Our team contacts you for consultation, evaluates your profile, and offers suitable vacancies."
      },
      {
        "q": "When will I know if I'm approved?",
        "a": "Employer decision usually comes within 1-2 weeks after the interview."
      },
      {
        "q": "Can I apply for Israel if I worked there before?",
        "a": "Yes, if you had no legal issues during your previous visit. Tell us all details during consultation."
      },
      {
        "q": "How do I contact WVG?",
        "a": "WhatsApp, phone, email or contact form. We work Mon-Fri 9:00-18:00."
      },
